# Purpose {-}
This lab introduces resonance in an RLC circuit.  

# Preliminary {-}
1. Write a Python program that computes the complex impedances of both the parallel ($Z_p$) and series ($Z_s$) [RLC circuits](#the-rlc-circuits) with a frequency range of $f\in [1kHz,100kHz]$.
2. Simulate both [RLC circuits](#the-rlc-circuits) in LTspice and generate complex impedance plots for $f\in [1kHz,100kHz]$.
3. Create the [series RLC circuit](#series-rlc-circuit) on a breadboard and measure the impedance of the circuit. Use python to graph the experimentally obtained impedance values.  

## Equipment {-}
- Breadboard
- Multimeter
- Wave Generator
- Oscilloscope
- Resistor: $1k\Omega$
- Inductor: $4.7mH$
- Capacitor: $0.033\mu F$

